While training, we have loss that is the sum of image to text loss and text to image loss and by using feedback mechanism, the losses are minimized by modifying the weights of the model.

Training loss = image to text loss + text to image loss


As CLIP is trained with internet data, it’s not suitable for fine grained tasks. For example, If two images has birds, this model cannot identify the name of the birds.



